question: Will Alabama have highest margin of victory for Trump in Super Tuesday Republican Primaries?
description:
Update: Per the rules, the margin for this market group is defined using votes for Trump and the next highest vote-getter: 
Trump / (# Trump + # Next highest) - # Next highest / (# Trump + # Next highest). The margin for this market group doesn’t take into consideration votes for other candidates.

This market will resolve to 'Yes' if Alabama has the highest margin of victory for Donald J. Trump in the 2024 Super Tuesday Republican Primaries among the states participating, excluding American Samoa. Otherwise, this market will resolve to “No”.

For the purpose of resolving this market, the 'margin of victory' is defined as the absolute difference between the percentages of votes received by Donald J. Trump and the second-place candidate. Percentages of the votes received by each candidate will be determined by dividing the total number of votes each of the two candidates receives by the sum of all votes received by both candidates in the election.

The states participating in the Super Tuesday Republican Primaries are: Alabama, Alaska, Arkansas, California, Colorado, Maine, Massachusetts, Minnesota, North Carolina, Oklahoma, Tennessee, Texas, Utah, Vermont, and Virginia.

The resolution source for this market will be the announcement of the primary results from the participating state Republican parties. However, a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.

question: Any rug >$1m on Blast today?
description:
This market asks whether or not any project on Blast will undergo a 'rug pull' event by February 29, 2024, 11:59 PM ET worth over >$1 million USD. A 'rug pull' is a fraudulent practice in the world of cryptocurrency, where developers abandon a project and run away with investors' funds.

If any project on Blast is reported to have executed a 'rug pull' worth >$1,000,000 in the form of sudden withdrawal of funds, abandonment of project, or otherwise shutting down with user funds still in their system by February 29, 2024, 11:59 PM ET, this market will resolve to "Yes". Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

The resolution of this market will be based on credible reports from trusted industry sources confirming the 'rug pull' event.

question: Will 'Ghostbusters: Frozen Empire' gross under $35m opening weekend?
description:
This is a market on how much 'Ghostbusters: Frozen Empire' (2024) will gross domestically on its opening weekend. The “Domestic Weekend” tab on https://www.boxofficemojo.com/title/tt21235248/ will be used to resolve this market once the values for the 3-day opening weekend (March 22 - March 24) are final (i.e. not studio estimates).

This market will resolve to "Yes" if 'Ghostbusters: Frozen Empire' (2024) grosses less than $35,000,000 on its 3-day opening weekend. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

Please note, this market will resolve according to the Box Office Mojo numbers under Domestic Weekend for the 3-day weekend (which typically includes Thursday's previews), regardless of whether domestic refers to only the USA, or to USA and Canada, etc.

If there is no final data available by March 28, 2024, 11:59 PM ET, another credible resolution source will be chosen.

question: Blast exploit by March 7?
description:
This is a market on whether Blast suffers an exploit by March 7, 2024, 11:59 PM ET.

The resolution source for this market will be the Rekt News leaderboard, currently available at https://rekt.news/leaderboard/.

If Blast is listed on the resolution source as having suffered an exploit before the resolution date, regardless of the size or ranking, this market will resolve to “Yes”. Otherwise, this market will resolve to “No”.

This market pertains to an exploit of Blast itself. Exploits of protocols on Blast will not count.

Only exploits which have a date listed on the Rekt News Leaderboard as March 7, 2024 or before will count. In the case there is ambiguity over the validity or availability of Rekt's Leaderboard, the project's primary communication channels (e.g. Twitter), and other credible crypto publications will be referenced.

question: Will Alaska be Trump's worst state on Super Tuesday?
description:
Update: Per the rules, the margin for this market group is defined using votes for Trump and the next highest vote-getter: 
Trump / (# Trump + # Next highest) - # Next highest / (# Trump + # Next highest). The margin for this market group doesn’t take into consideration votes for other candidates.

This market will resolve to "Yes" if Donald J. Trump performs worse in the Alaska Republican primary compared to all other states participating in the 2024 Super Tuesday Republican Primaries. Otherwise, this market will resolve to “No”.

Trump's worst performance will be considered as either the smallest margin of victory if Trump wins all super Tuesday primaries, or largest margin of defeat if Trump loses one or more primaries.

‘Margin' is defined as the difference between the percentages of votes received by Donald J. Trump and the second-highest vote-getter. Percentages of the votes received by each of the two candidates will be determined by dividing the total number of votes each receives by the sum of all votes received by both candidates in the election.

The states participating in the Super Tuesday Republican Primaries are: Alabama, Alaska, Arkansas, California, Colorado, Maine, Massachusetts, Minnesota, North Carolina, Oklahoma, Tennessee, Texas, Utah, Vermont, and Virginia excluding American Samoa.

The resolution source for this market will be the announcement of the primary results from the participating state Republican parties. However, a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.
